<div class="card s" id="sec-resolved">
<h3 style="color:var(--gb);font-size:13px">1. Resolved Questions (from CNH)</h3>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q1:</strong> ASCII string protocol, MID() parsing — confirmed by reference code.</div>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q2:</strong> PLC = TCP SERVER (listener). ProPlanner = TCP CLIENT (initiator).</div>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q3:</strong> No storage — OPTIX recipe managers for pass/fail criteria entry only.</div>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q5:</strong> CNH is using ProPlanner, not full Pivotware deployment.</div>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q6:</strong> ProPlanner handles serial number tracking independently.</div>
<div class="rv"><strong>Q8:</strong> ProPlanner only needs PASS/FAIL — not full force/distance signatures.</div>
